          "severity": "extensive/rapidly progressive",
          "criteria": "large BSA, active spreading, non-face resistant",
          "treatment": "NB-UVB phototherapy 2-3x/week (first-line for widespread). Oral corticosteroids for rapidly progressive (<3 months). Systemic immunosuppressants rarely. Depigmentation therapy (monobenzone) for >80% BSA."
